Subject: [PATCH] no-frame-refocus-cocoa (Emacs 30.x)

Adapted from d12frosted/homebrew-emacs-plus emacs-28 no-frame-refocus
patch. Emacs 30 refactored the post-`delete_frame` NS focus block to
call `ns_make_frame_key_window` instead of `Fraise_frame`; this patch
removes the equivalent block under the new code.

When deleting a frame on macOS, Emacs picks another frame and forces it
to become the key window. With multiple visible frames (or the daemon)
that yanks focus to an unrelated frame. Removing the call leaves focus
to whatever the OS / window manager chooses.

--- a/src/frame.c
+++ b/src/frame.c
@@ -2212,19 +2212,6 @@
 		}
 	    }
 	}
-#ifdef NS_IMPL_COCOA
-      else
-	{
-	  /* Under NS, there is no system mechanism for choosing a new
-	     window to get focus -- it is left to application code.
-	     So the portion of THIS application interfacing with NS
-	     needs to make the frame we switch to the key window.  */
-	  struct frame *f1 = XFRAME (frame1);
-	  if (FRAME_NS_P (f1))
-	    ns_make_frame_key_window (f1);
-	}
-#endif
-
       do_switch_frame (frame1, 0, 1, Qnil);
       sf = SELECTED_FRAME ();
     }
